<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="382" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1646,1995]" box="[151,820,1646,1671]" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1646,1671]" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Description.</emphasis>
Body length. (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount box="[691,714,1647,1670]" pageId="4" pageNumber="382" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 7.2 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1646,1995]" box="[199,1158,1682,1707]" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Overall coloration bright yellow, without dark spots; forewing membrane translucent.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1646,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">
Ocelli separated by about 5 times distance from ocellus to adjacent eye; clypeal suture prominent, anteclypeus central arched, base front width exceeds the apex (
<figureCitation box="[717,784,1754,1779]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9. 1, 4, 7" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1797,1819]" captionTargetBox="[340,1219,675,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[340,1247,675,1768]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. 1, 4, 7 Siniassus hamulus sp. nov.; 2, 5, 8. Decliviassus sagittatus sp. nov.; 3, 6, 9. Krisna quadrimaculosus sp. nov.; 1–3. Dorsal view; 4–6. Lateral view; 7–9. Facial view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1303709/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Scutellum wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1186,1754,1779]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9. 1, 4, 7" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1797,1819]" captionTargetBox="[340,1219,675,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[340,1247,675,1768]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. 1, 4, 7 Siniassus hamulus sp. nov.; 2, 5, 8. Decliviassus sagittatus sp. nov.; 3, 6, 9. Krisna quadrimaculosus sp. nov.; 1–3. Dorsal view; 4–6. Lateral view; 7–9. Facial view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1303709/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1646,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,1790,1815]" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer side ship-shaped, gradually narrowed from base to apex, with numerous macrosetae distally (
<figureCitation box="[250,335,1826,1851]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[357,1218,955,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[340,1248,944,1910]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–42. Decliviassus sagittatus sp. nov., 37. Pygofer, lateral view; 38. Subgenital plate and ventral pygofer appendage, ventral view; 39. Style, ventral view; 40. Connective, ventral view; 41. Aedeagus, lateral view; 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1303717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate short and broad, triangular, pygofer ventral process short, apex curved slightly ventrad and mesad (
<figureCitation box="[382,521,1862,1887]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[357,1218,955,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[340,1248,944,1910]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–42. Decliviassus sagittatus sp. nov., 37. Pygofer, lateral view; 38. Subgenital plate and ventral pygofer appendage, ventral view; 39. Style, ventral view; 40. Connective, ventral view; 41. Aedeagus, lateral view; 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1303717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Figs. 37–38</figureCitation>
). Connective straplike, simple (
<figureCitation box="[882,968,1862,1887]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[357,1218,955,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[340,1248,944,1910]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–42. Decliviassus sagittatus sp. nov., 37. Pygofer, lateral view; 38. Subgenital plate and ventral pygofer appendage, ventral view; 39. Style, ventral view; 40. Connective, ventral view; 41. Aedeagus, lateral view; 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1303717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Style slender, close to the apex slightly bending outwards apically (
<figureCitation box="[466,552,1898,1923]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[357,1218,955,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[340,1248,944,1910]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–42. Decliviassus sagittatus sp. nov., 37. Pygofer, lateral view; 38. Subgenital plate and ventral pygofer appendage, ventral view; 39. Style, ventral view; 40. Connective, ventral view; 41. Aedeagus, lateral view; 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1303717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus hairpin-shaped in lateral aspect, apex almost membranous; dorsal apodeme bifurcate in ventral aspect, shaft apex arrow-shaped; gonopore apical between bases of paired processes (
<figureCitation box="[159,297,1970,1995]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–42" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[357,1218,955,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[340,1248,944,1910]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–42. Decliviassus sagittatus sp. nov., 37. Pygofer, lateral view; 38. Subgenital plate and ventral pygofer appendage, ventral view; 39. Style, ventral view; 40. Connective, ventral view; 41. Aedeagus, lateral view; 42. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1303717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="382">Figs. 41–42</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
